  schema:name "Errico Malatesta" ;
  schema:description "Errico Malatesta (1853–1932) was an Italian anarcho-communist whose lifelong organizing and writing emphasized the inseparability of theory and practice, the necessity of insurrection, and the organizational discipline required for effective anarchist action." ;
